node.title: Health authorities concerned there could be an undetected COVID case on the Gold Coast
node.alt: A side shot of a shopping centre with a christmas tree outside.
node.description: The genomic sequencing on a man who tested positive to coronavirus on Wednesday finds the case is not linked to any another local cases, with authorities believing the virus was spread by an unknown interstate "incursion".Â
node.content: ["Genomic tests have revealed the latest COVID-19 case detected on the Gold Coast is not linked to any recent local cases there.", "Acting Chief Health Officer Peter Aitken said he believed\u00a0it had\u00a0been transmitted through an unknown interstate \"incursion\".", "There were no new community cases of the virus reported today, however there were two cases in home quarantine and four in hotel quarantine.", "Dr Aitken said genomic sequencing on\u00a0the man who tested positive on the Gold Coast on Wednesday\u00a0has today linked the case to previous outbreaks in New South Wales.", "\"We don't know how he got it at this stage,\" Dr Aitken said.", "\"The most likely cause is there has been an incursion somewhere from New South Wales.", "\"We need to make sure that no-one else on the Gold Coast has been exposed and may have COVID there.\"", "Health Minister Yvette D'Ath encouraged people on the Gold Coast to get tested and vaccinated.", "\"[The recent case]\u00a0means someone has been on the Gold Coast and may still be on there, or elsewhere in Queensland, who is positive and haven't been identified as yet,\" she said.", "She said 2,154 people were tested for the virus in the region in the past 24 hours.", "\"So this reinforces the importance of everyone coming forward if you've got any symptoms, no matter how mild, to get tested, and importantly, getting those vaccination rates up.\"", "Ms D'Ath said there would be no new border restrictions placed on South Australia despite an outbreak there, but she said authorities were \"closely\" monitoring the situation."]
